messages.message: Found that js file download sometimes takes a couple of minutes to complete coz of the big size... Is there a reason why these files are not minified/compressed ? Who can look into this ?
these bundles are already minimized (see screenshot from dogfood), what environment are you using?
Probably we should plan to remove unused/old apps. That may be reduce the shared modules

@Serena this is in our saas environments :slightly_smiling_face:

@jayapandian.ponraj we are only downloading 2.8MB of content.  We should not take a minute to download that much amount of content?  I think that the content is served directly from nginx, so the request shouldn’t even be reaching our webstack.  Can this be due to some type of “warming” up of services in the network stack?
